        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 3 at 6:40PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 640 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from near Epworth to near Mountaintown, and moving east at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Ellijay, Blue Ridge, East Ellijay, Morganton, Jones Mill, Higdon,
Loving, Epworth, Pisgah, Mineral Bluff, Cherry Log, Mountaintown, and
Colwell.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately.</instruction>
